        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">REVISION DESCRIPTION</emph>
                    - Production dates added
                </para>
                <para>The IROS suspension (International Ride Optimized Suspension) uses an auxiliary leaf spring which
                    in some cases may generate a rattling noise by contacting the main leaf spring. The auxiliary leaf
                    spring is an integral part of the IROS system and must not be removed.
                    <revst/>
                    Beginning April 6, 2005, the auxiliary spring camber was changed to eliminate the spring rattle.
                    <revend/>The rattling does not affect the proper operation of either the main or auxiliary leaf
                    springs.
                </para>
                <para>If the rattling noise is an issue on chassis built prior to April 6, 2005, a service kit is
                    available.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
