        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="3">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage, personal injury, or death, park the vehicle on a flat level surface,
                        set the parking brake, turn the engine off, and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the items shown in Figure 1. One or more, as needed,
                    <emph type="bold">Delrin Spacers</emph>
                    are to be installed between the auxiliary leaf spring and the main leaf spring.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install one
                    <emph type="bold">Delrin Spacer</emph>
                    and a
                    <emph type="bold">Steel Plate</emph>
                    on the outside surface of the main leaf spring and auxiliary leaf spring as shown in Figure 1. Make
                    sure the
                    <emph type="bold">Delrin Spacer</emph>
                    is placed between the
                    <emph type="bold">Steel Plate</emph>
                    and the spring.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two (2)
                    <emph type="bold">M8 Bolts and Nuts</emph>
                    as shown in Figure 2. Align the spacer/steel plate assembly as shown in Figure 3. Tighten the
                    fasteners to 15 to 19 Lbf-ft (20 to 26 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repeat this procedure on all other IROS springs on this vehicle.</para>
            </step1>
